    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@eunjae-lee I'm having trouble with this feature using the latest instantsearch.js on Chrome on Mac (latest) - The scroll position isn't restored. However, Safari works fine, even on iOS for me. History within the same page (going back) works as expected though.\r\n\r\n- https://infinitehits-cache-m86tvb8nd.now.sh/ - doesn't work in Chrome\r\n- https://infinite-hits-cache-react.now.sh/ - works in all browsers\r\n\r\nI tried locally, linking to a local `detail.html` to check if it had anything to do with switching to an external domain (google in the original example). Routing is enabled, so I don't know what's different from the React version.\r\n\r\n**UPDATE**\r\n\r\nI was able to make the non-React example work by explicitly saving and restoring the scroll position:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst search = instantsearch({\r\n  indexName: 'instant_search',\r\n  searchClient,\r\n  routing: true,\r\n});\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidgets([/* setup widgets */]);\r\n\r\nwindow.onbeforeunload = function(e) {\r\n  localStorage.setItem('scrollpos', window.scrollY);\r\n};\r\n\r\nsearch.once('render', () => {\r\n  const scrollpos = localStorage.getItem('scrollpos');\r\n  if (scrollpos) window.scrollTo(0, scrollpos);\r\n});\r\n\r\nsearch.start();\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
